The reason why this board has popups and banner advertisement is because the people behind EZBoard want to make a little bit of money to keep things rolling (and pay themselves for the work it entails). The money for keeping these ads away (&quot;Gold Status&quot;) comes from both PKBBS community members and Patrick, the man behind Polykarbon. The fact that we currently don't have gold status is because there haven't been enough donations to renew it yet. As soon as there's enough donations, we'll get gold status back.<br>
<br>
The last time we were collecting donations to get gold status back, I was suggesting similar things as you are suggesting now - anti-popup programs and even local proxy servers that filter out advertisement. Unfortunately it wasn't and isn't the right solution to the problem. EZBoard pays for their hardware and staff with both donations and the revenue (the little of it) they get from advertisement. If one or the other is lost, they're in trouble. And the latter one is lost when people use anti-advertisement software.<br>
<br>
Personally I DO use Opera's (just about the best web browser there is) popup filtering because pop-ups ARE annoying. I don't, however, use advertisement removing proxy software anymore and thus see the banners that are now displayed on the site. This is all very well and good, but I ALSO contribute to the PKBBS community chest when possible. I did it the last time and I've done it this time too (the donation's being processed currently).<br>
<br>
While I'm sure your suggestion was ment as helpful advice, its kind is generally frowned upon on this board. I learned this the hard way myself some months back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I therefore recommend you refrain from posting this message in any other threads on these boards (although I am Just Another User on these boards, not a moderator). Your choice of thread was pretty poor in the first place, as this is a thread (and board) for c&amp;c'ing people's artwork, not for advertising software / websites (which is also frowned upon when done without the moderators' permission). <p><hr><b>Want to color my lineart?</b> Otherwise alter something I've created? Read my <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujspuonti.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><b>profile</b></a> for further information before proceeding!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujspuonti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JSPuonti</A> at: 9/2/02 3:58:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urybolton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rybolton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/3/02 2:10:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7060.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Junko all done up and lookin good</span><hr size=1> I can see that help in the area of popup ad's is not wanted here.  I only mentioned it for the good of those with a low tolerance for popup advertising.  I think that there are plenty less annoying ways to have advertising on the web, and if everyone blocked popup advertising it would cease to exist.  Maybe a few services would go away, but I'm sure other forms of Internet advertising would replace the anno